cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CE, cs.NE, cs.CV

The paper discusses the use of machine learning models for predicting disease progression in Alzheimer's patients using electronic health data. This falls under the broad category of machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The specific model used, Conditional Restricted Boltzmann Machine, is a type of neural network and falls under the sub-category of neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the use of clinical variables and laboratory tests, which could fall under the sub-category of computer vision (cs.CV) or computational epidemiology (cs.CE).
